[2
Date: 4 Jan 2001 15:42:14 -0500
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: La Nacion (Costa Rica), 4 Jan 2001 [translated and edited by Mod.MPP
<http://www.nacion.co.cr/ln_ee/2001/enero/04/pais8.html>

Deaths in Limon, Costa Rica: Results of Tests Awaited
-----------------------------------------------------
LIMON: Although authorities of the Costa Rican Ministry of Health stated
that 2 recent deaths in Limon were not caused by dengue hemorrhagic fever,
Alvaro Duran, the Medical Director of the Tony Facio Hospital, said that
the laboratory results that would help to eliminate the possibility of
dengue hemorrhagic fever, or other virus [infections, were still pending.
Duran added that he suspects that the cases correspond to the same febrile
picture that, in past months, killed an eastern woman in the same province.
In this case he indicated tests were sent to a laboratory in the United
States, but results have not been received as yet.
[Byline: Israel Oconitrillo
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Dengue hemorrhagic fever deaths would not be unexpected following the
introduction of a dengue virus serotype not previously prevalent in a
population. The results of the laboratory tests are awaited with interest.
If the deaths are not attributed to dengue hemorrhagic fever, then what is
the diagnosis? - Mod.CP
